{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778348461,"nonce":"u92paiVfJg7ueSEL0CZkOG2LZCA=","message":"## Comprehensive results — anti-anticipation 6-cell matrix\n\nBranch `feature/anti-anticipation-6cell-results` (commit `b5e6e6c`) — auth `0ae6fdc9` merged.\n\n### Setup recap\n- 6 cells × 5 GRU replicates × 12,000 warmup batches × batch size 250\n- Single GPU (RTX 5090, EUR-IS-2), 6 cells in parallel, ~40 min wall-clock, ~$1\n- All cells: jerk loss 1e5, seed=42; varies in anti-anticipation lever and loss-shape config\n- Cells (with their unique levers):\n  | # | Cell | Lever |\n  |---|---|---|\n  | 1 | `gru__jerk` | control |\n  | 2 | `gru__jerk_motor_pre` | + `nn_output_pre_go=1e-2` |\n  | 3 | `gru__jerk_smooth_high` | + `nn_hidden_derivative=1e2` |\n  | 4 | `gru__jerk_motor_smooth_combo` | both 2 + 3 |\n  | 5 | `gru__jerk_loss_v_terminal` | Variant A: terminal velocity (no late-vel running) |\n  | 6 | `gru__jerk_loss_historical` | Variant B: (t/N)^6 + cliff, full historical shape |\n\n### Training loss (final-batch weighted total, mean ± std across 5 replicates)\n\n| Cell | End loss | std | std/mean |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Control | 7.34 | 1.43 | 0.19 |\n| Pre-go motor mask | 5.55 | 0.37 | 0.07 |\n| Hidden smoothness 1e2 | **3.28** | 0.16 | 0.05 |\n| Pre-go + smooth (combo) | 4.15 | 0.33 | 0.08 |\n| Variant A | 5.97 | 0.87 | 0.15 |\n| Variant B | 13.52 | 4.98 | 0.37 |\n\n(Cross-cell loss values are NOT directly comparable — cells have different loss configurations.)\n\n### Plot bug + cell-2 spike resolution\n\nThe first total-loss plot was wrong. The prior subagent called `jt.leaves(history.loss)` on the `TermTree` and filtered `ndim==2`, picking up the *unweighted* leaf arrays. Some terms have weight 1e-5 but raw values 100-8000 (`nn_hidden`, `nn_output`), which dominated the false \"total\" but contribute almost nothing to the real loss. Reloaded properly via `init_task_trainer_history` skeleton; corrected curves match the validation-loss reports during training (5-25 range).\n\nApparent downward spikes in cell-2 in the broken plot were artifacts of the unweighted leaf sum. In the true total loss for cell 2 there are no real spikes (min-to-50-batch-median = 0.72; smooth improvement). See `notes/cell2_spike_investigation.md`.\n\nA subtle real finding from cell 2: `nn_output_pre_go` weighted contribution **rises monotonically** through training (~2e-4 → ~0.16). The 1e-2 penalty does NOT collapse pre-go activity to zero; it just slows growth. Sufficient to reduce hold drift but not to eliminate it.\n\n### Variance + anticipation analysis (CV = SD/mean of peak forward velocity, across replicates)\n\n| Cell | Mean PV (m/s) | SD PV | **CV** | Hold drift (mm) | TTP (steps) |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Control | 0.577 | 0.074 | 0.129 | 19.8 ± 4.2 | 61.9 |\n| Pre-go motor mask | 0.840 | 0.062 | 0.073 | 5.5 ± 0.5 | 61.6 |\n| Hidden smoothness 1e2 | 1.071 | 0.006 | **0.006** | 35.7 ± 1.5 | 47.4 |\n| **Pre-go + smooth (combo)** | **1.222** | **0.008** | **0.007** | **4.6 ± 0.3** | 52.6 |\n| Variant A | 0.598 | 0.084 | 0.141 | 19.1 ± 4.7 | 62.6 |\n| Variant B | 0.619 | 0.118 | 0.190 | 16.0 ± 2.2 | 66.4 |\n\n### Per-cell findings\n- **Pre-go motor mask alone**: suppresses hold drift to 5.5 mm (72% of control); residual anticipation remains. CV 0.073.\n- **Hidden smoothness 1e2 alone**: collapses replicate variance dramatically (CV 0.006) — replicates land on essentially identical attractors — but **anticipation drift increases by 80%** (35.7 mm). The smoothness penalty seems to encourage maintaining preparatory activity over a longer pre-go window.\n- **Combo (motor_pre + smooth_high)**: wins on every measured axis. CV 0.007 (variance fully collapsed), drift 4.6 mm (anticipation suppressed), peak velocity 1.22 m/s (~2× control — the smoothness lever produces faster, more ballistic reaches).\n- **Variant A**: no improvement on either metric vs control.\n- **Variant B**: worst on both metrics. Historical loss shape did not deliver here.\n\n### Conclusion\nCombo cell (jerk + pre-go motor mask + hidden smoothness 1e2) is the clear winner of this matrix on the metrics measured. Hidden smoothness is the dominant variance-collapse lever; the motor_pre penalty is needed to suppress the anticipation that smoothness alone introduces. Loss-shape variants (A, B) are deprioritized as anti-anticipation levers.\n\n**Residual anticipation remains in the combo cell** (4.6 mm vs ~0 ideal) — next lever to investigate.\n\n### Methodological caveat (CRITICAL)\nThe pre-reg threshold `\u003c0.5` was set against the prior `baseline_jerk_vrnn_matrix` matrix's best of 0.76, which is a **pairwise profile-RMSE ratio** (within-cell trajectory RMSE / nearest-neighbor across-cell RMSE). This analysis uses **CV = SD/mean of peak velocity scalar**. Different metrics: profile shape similarity vs peak-velocity scalar tightness. Every cell here passes \u003c0.5 trivially on CV; the threshold doesn't discriminate. Cross-comparison with prior cannot be done without recomputing one matrix on the other's metric — flagged on `4d38c15`.\n\n### Outputs\nTracked in `results/part2_5/runpod/anti_anticipation_loss_shape_6cell/`:\n- `runs/\u003cgroup\u003e__\u003cvariant\u003e/run.json` × 6\n- `notes/variance_analysis.md`, `notes/cell2_spike_investigation.md`\n- `figures/{training_loss,training_loss_per_term,peak_velocity_distributions,forward_velocity_profiles,hold_drift_profiles}/spec.json` × 5\n\nHTML renders (gitignored, local-only) at `_artifacts/.../figures/\u003cname\u003e/figure.html`.\n\nScripts: `plot_training_loss_6cell.py`, `analyse_anti_anticipation_6cell_variance.py`.\n\n### Cross-refs\n- `c99ad9d` (training-methods) — combo as candidate default; loss-shape variants deprioritized\n- `4d38c15` (analyses) — variance-metric mismatch needs reconciliation\n- `fdad09d` (rlrmp feature) — `train_minimax.py` should auto-write `run.json`\n- `40f8322` (feedbax feature) — `loss_history_compare` multi-run plot utility","files":null}]}